cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the task of selection in 3D point clouds using a deep neural network. This involves processing large amounts of visual data, which suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new deep learning approach to solve the problem, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses a hierarchical network architecture and farthest point sampling to improve scalability, which suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
